          "instruction": "Answer the questions based on the audio.",
          "prompt_html": "<h1>NOTE COMPLETION 18</h1><p><strong>Questions 26 - 30</strong></p><p>Complete the notes. Use <strong>NO MORE THAN FOUR WORDS AND / OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer.</p><p><strong>Australian Immigration</strong></p><table><thead><tr><th>Two Current Immigration Programmes</th><th>1 The Migration Programme</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td></td><td>2 The Humanitarian Programme</td></tr></tbody></table><p>1 The Migration Programme</p><p>To get Australian permanent residence, immigrants must be either:</p><table><thead><tr><th></th><th>- <blank data-qid=\"q26\"/><br>-</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td></td><td>OR</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>- sponsored by a family member currently resident in Australia</td></tr></tbody></table><p>2004-05 Migration Programme has 120,000 places available.</p><p>2 The Humanitarian Programme</p><p>Two components designed for refugees and others in special humanitarian need:</p><table><thead><tr><th></th><th>1 <blank data-qid=\"q27\"/><br>:</th><th>assists people overseas in humanitarian need</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td></td><td>2 Other component:</td><td>People in Australia on temporary visas / without permission claiming asylum</td></tr></tbody></table><p>2004 and 2005 Humanitarian Programme has <blank data-qid=\"q28\"/> places available.</p><p>Australian Illegal Migrants</p><p>These are people who:</p><ul><li>enter Australia without authority.</li><li><blank data-qid=\"q29\"/>.</li><li>work without appropriate approval.</li><li>have their visas cancelled and stay.</li></ul><p>Australia’s Migration Act 1958: All non Australian citizens unlawfully in Australia to be detained and <blank data-qid=\"q30\"/> unless given permission to remain.</p>",
